## Summary

Implemented `hive resume` — a session recovery command for AgentHive (US-007).

### What was built

**`src/commands/resume.ts`** — New command that:
- Detects each agent's state by checking lock files (PID alive/dead/missing) and tmux windows
- Categorizes agents as `running`, `stale` (orphaned lock), or `stopped`
- Displays a color-coded recovery plan showing what action will be taken for each agent
- Cleans stale locks and orphaned tmux windows before relaunching
- Reuses the existing tmux session — adds windows rather than creating a new one
- Supports `--yes` (skip prompt), `--force` (restart running agents), `--dry-run` (plan only)

**Also updated:**
- `src/index.ts` — registered `registerResumeCommand`
- `src/commands/completion.ts` — added bash, zsh, and fish completions for `resume`

### Quality gates
- `npm run typecheck` — passed
- `npm test` — 154 tests passed (7 suites)
- `npm run build` — compiled successfully

